\end{figure}




\subsubsection{Non self-dual, primitive nebentypus}\label{sec:repulsion3}
Let $f$ be a primitive holomorphic cusp form of weight 2 and level 13 and with primitive  nebentypus that is not self-dual (LMFDB label: \texttt{13.2.e.a}).  Let $\mathcal{D}(X)$ be defined as in Definition 4 for $f\ne\overline f$.  We calculate the distribution of the lowest zero for $L(s,f\otimes\psi_d)$ for $d <X$ for $X=40000$ and $d\equiv\diamondsuit \pmod{13}$ .  The basic statistics of the distributions are reported in Table~\ref{tbl:nonself-dual} and density plots for the distributions are seen in Figure~\ref{fig:nonself-dual}.  As expected, the centers of these distributions decraease as $d$ increases.

